'''Ogana Major''', or '''Ogana''', was a huge blue [[Planet]] in the [[Kessil system]]. It was orbited by five [[Moons|moons]], including the [[Fourth Moon of Utapau|Fourth Moon of Ogana]].<ref name="first">{{WebCite|url=https://www.starwarz.com/starkiller/the-star-wars-revised-first-draft|text=''The Star Wars: First Draft''|work=[https://www.starwarz.com/starkiller Starkiller — The Jedi Bendu Script Site]|archivedate=20240904070909}}</ref>

It was the homeworld of [[Kane Starkiller|The Starkiller]], and was destroyed by the [[Galactic Empire (The Star Wars)|Galactic Empire]] before [[Luke Skywalker|Luke Starkiller]] could reach it.<ref name="second">{{WebCite|url=https://www.starwarz.com/starkiller/adventures-of-the-starkiller-second-draft|text=Adventures of the Starkiller, Episode I: The Star Wars|archivedate=20240818175509}}</ref>

It was a desert world, above which Princess [[Leia (The Star Wars)|Leia]] was captured by the Empire.<ref name="synopsis">''[[The Making of Star Wars: The Definitive Story Behind the Original Film]], Adventures of Luke Starkiller: Episode I: The Star Wars story synopsis summary''</ref>

==Behind the scenes==
"Ogana" replaced [[Utapau (Kessil system)|Utapau]] in the [[The Star Wars first draft|first draft]] of the script for [[Star Wars: Episode IV A New Hope|''A New Hope'']].<ref name="first" /> In the [[Adventures of the Starkiller, Episode I: The Star Wars|second draft]], Ogana Major was the name for what would become the planet [[Alderaan]].<ref name="second" /> It became known as "Organa" in the synopsis of the third draft and again stood in for the future [[Tatooine]].<ref name="synopsis" /> In the [[The Star Wars: From The Adventures of Luke Starkiller|third draft]], Organa Major had the role that Ogana Major had in the second draft and was Leia's homeworld. Additionally, [[House of Organa|Organa]] was [[Leia Skywalker Organa Solo|Leia's]] surname in the third draft<ref name="third">{{WebCite|url=https://www.starwarz.com/starkiller/the-star-wars-from-the-adventures-of-luke-starkiller-third-draft|text=The Star Wars: From The Adventures of Luke Starkiller|archivedate=20240818094359}}</ref> and all subsequent drafts. In the fourth draft and all subsequent drafts, the planet called Organa Major in the third draft was called Alderaan.<ref name="fourth">{{WebCite|url=https://www.starwarz.com/starkiller/star-wars-the-adventures-of-luke-starkiller-as-taken-from-the-journal-of-the-whills|text=''The Adventures of Luke Starkiller as taken from the Journal of the Whills: Saga I: The Star Wars'', fourth draft|archivedate=20240518135003}}</ref>

